<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading"><strong>FAQ About Taxes on Lottery Winnings<=
/strong></h2>



<p>Still have more questions about lottery taxes? Find some answers to comm=
on questions below.</p>



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading"><strong>Do Lottery Winnings Count as Income?=
</strong></h3>



<p>Lottery and other <a href=3D"https://turbotax.intuit.com/tax-tips/jobs-a=
nd-career/how-to-pay-taxes-on-gambling-winnings-and-losses/L7JNH7mjn">gambl=
ing winnings</a> are considered taxable income by the IRS. As such, you=E2=
=80=99ll need to report the value of your winnings as =E2=80=9COther Income=
=E2=80=9D on your annual return using <a href=3D"https://turbotax.intuit.co=
m/tax-tips/irs-tax-return/video-when-to-use-tax-form-1040/L4a3T1smv">Form 1=
040</a>.</p>



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading"><strong>Do Lottery Winnings Count as Income =
for Social Security?</strong></h3>



<p>If you win big in the lottery while collecting Social Security, your win=
nings won=E2=80=99t be counted as income that can reduce your benefits. Ear=
ning a regular income while receiving Social Security, however, may reduce =
your benefits.</p>



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading"><strong>Are Lottery Winnings Taxed Twice?</s=
trong></h3>



<p>Because lottery winnings are considered taxable income, they=E2=80=99re =
subject to taxes at the state and federal levels just like regular income. =
Whether or not you pay state income taxes on your lottery prize depends on =
the state you file in.</p>



<p><strong>Closing:</strong></p>



<p class=3D"disclaimer">Winning the lottery is a life-changing event that m=
ay afford you newfound wealth and opportunities. With that being said, it=
=E2=80=99s important to be aware of how lottery winnings are taxed, so you=
=E2=80=99re not surprised by the amount of winnings you actually receive.Us=
e our lottery calculator to get an estimate of the taxes withheld and find =
out how much you=E2=80=99ll actually keep. Once the next <a href=3D"https:/=
/blog.turbotax.intuit.com/tax-planning-2/when-is-tax-season-how-to-get-ahea=
d-before-its-here-48381/">tax season</a> rolls around, use <a href=3D"https=
://turbotax.intuit.com/personal-taxes/online/">TurboTax</a> to help you rep=
ort your income as accurately as possible. Don=E2=80=99t forget to connect =
with a <a href=3D"https://turbotax.intuit.com/personal-taxes/online/turbota=
x-live.jsp">TurboTax Experts</a> tax expert if you have any tax questions t=
hat need answers.</p>
